SETTING UP A NEW GITHUB REPO FOR A NEW PROJECT


1. Open the terminal in VS Code, that is the folder of your projrct. 
   and run  >>>> git init

2. >> git add .

3. git commit -m "Initial commit"

4. Create a Repository on GitHub , Use GitHubâ€™s CLI (Git Hub CMD): >>>> gh repo create <repo-name>

5. Return to your project terminal and >>>>> git remote add origin https://github.com/<username>/<repo-name>.git


6. While in the project terminal >>>> git push -u origin main




